The paper deals with a machine learning algorithm for prediction with expert advice, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of loss functions and scoring rules suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of decision theory and game theory, which are covered by cs.DS and cs.GT. The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in the presence of changing and diverse loss functions, which may be related to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and the study of diversity and heterogeneity in machine learning (cs.SI).
